transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I had placed an order a little while back and I just received it today and it's not what I ordered.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me help you out, Chester. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 12-22-1958.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Okay, can you please tell me what's imprinted on the individual pill?

Speaker 1: It is an AGV.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay, got it. Toss those in the trash can.

Speaker 1: The pharmacy made an error.

Speaker 2: Or the pharmacy probably ran out of AGVs to tell us and sent you generics.

Speaker 1: Give me one second. I'm going to put in a replacement order.

Speaker 2: And then I'm going to tell you how you can confirm you received the correct medication.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. All right.

Speaker 2: Okay, so when you get this new bottle in the mail,

Speaker 1: it's going to say AGV on the bottle, but it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 2: And Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 1: And then on the pill, the only number imprinted is the number 100.

Speaker 2: And those are the two ways you can confirm you received the Pfizer FDA-approved Pfizer-Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: And you can just toss those generics in the trash can.

Speaker 2: Now, they're already paid for, right, since I already paid?

Speaker 1: Yeah, but I'm sending you exactly the same, just the correct medication for your charge.

Speaker 2: I mean, go ahead and keep them, but yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'm not going to owe anything more, right?

Speaker 2: No, no, no. No, no, no. That was the pharmacy there. No.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Do you know when they'll ship it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, they'll ship it out to you tomorrow morning.

Speaker 2: And then they'll email you a tracking number.

Speaker 1: You should get it in about five days or less.

Speaker 2: I don't know, with the storm, because they're in Kentucky, maybe seven days or less.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: But they'll email you a tracking number, yeah.

Speaker 1: And they'll ship it out first thing tomorrow morning.

Speaker 2: Okay. Does this happen very often?

Speaker 1: Yeah, sometimes they run out because it's in such high demand.

Speaker 2: So it comes from Pfizer's manufacturer in France called Greenstone.

Speaker 1: So we have it shipped from there to our pharmacy in Kentucky.

Speaker 2: And sometimes they have so many orders, they send generics, and they don't tell us, which creates problems.

Speaker 1: But we get it fixed. So yeah, I apologize about that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because I can get the regular...

Speaker 1: Yeah, exactly. Like, why would you bother?

Speaker 2: I can get that for a lot cheaper than this price, I can tell you that.

Speaker 1: Exactly. Yeah.

Speaker 2: No, I understand your frustration.

Speaker 1: But no, I'm getting you out the correct stuff.

Speaker 2: You'll get it in a few days.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
